# Terminology-migration diff: draft-ietf-schc-over-ppp-00 -> SCHC Architecture -06

# Purpose: migrate the draft's terminology and architectural framing to
# draft-ietf-schc-architecture-06 while preserving all technical behavior.
# Adaptation need is None, so no diff location depends on an unaccepted
# Architecture change. Only terminology / framing text is changed; the profile
# parameters (RuleID numbering, No-ACK fragmentation, padding, MAX_PACKET_SIZE)
# and the IPV6CP/URI signaling are preserved unchanged.
#
# Diff is chunked by document section. Unchanged sections, boilerplate,
# acknowledgments, normative references, and administrative metadata are omitted
# except where a terminology change reaches them.


## Section 1 - Introduction

- The "SCHC Architecture" [I-D.pelov-lpwan-architecture] enables a peer
- to peer SCHC operation in addition to the classical device to network
- LPWAN paradigm, e.g., over a PPP connection.  To enable SCHC over PPP
- and therefore Ethernet and Wi-Fi, this specification extends
- [RFC5172] to signal SCHC as an additional compression method for use
- over PPP.
+ The "SCHC Architecture" [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture] enables a peer-
+ to-peer SCHC operation in addition to the classical Device-to-network
+ LPWAN paradigm, e.g., over a PPP connection.  In the terms of that
+ architecture, each peer runs a SCHC Endpoint that hosts one SCHC
+ Instance, the two Instances share a common Context, and they
+ communicate within a SCHC Session carried over the PPP connection.  To
+ enable SCHC over PPP and therefore Ethernet and Wi-Fi, this
+ specification extends [RFC5172] to signal SCHC as an additional
+ compression method for use over PPP.


